Subject: Bug fix in getsys.c


In RIPEM 1.3a2 in getsys.c there is the section:

#ifdef UNIX
         if( homedir[strlen (homedir) - 1] != '/')
            StrConcatRealloc (&homedir, "/");
#elif MSDOS
         if( homedir[strlen (homedir) - 1] != '\\' &&
            homedir[strlen (homedir) - 1] != ':' )
            StrConcatRealloc (&homedir, "\\");
#else /* MACTC */
         if( homedir[strlen (homedir) - 1] != ':')
            StrConcatRealloc (&homedir, ":");
#endif

The "elif MSDOS" should be "elif defined (MSDOS)".

- Jeff
